definition.value: An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-docosanoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.
A UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamate(4-) in which the muramoyl fragment has alpha-configuration at its anomeric centre; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-(2-hydroxybehenoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-(2-hydroxytetracosanoyl)-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.
Trianion of UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-L-lysine; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 22 carbons and 1 double bond.
A UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminoheptanedioate(4-) in which the muramoyl moiety has alpha-configuratijon at its anomeric centre; major species at pH 7.3
A (1E)-1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)pent-1-en-3-ol that is the (S)-enantiomer of diniconazole.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 22 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons and 1 double bond.
A member of the class of triazoles that is 4,4-dimethyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)pent-1-en-3-ol substituted at position 1 by a 2,4-dichlorophenyl group.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.

A (1E)-1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-4,4-dimethyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)pent-1-en-3-ol that is the active R-enantiomer of diniconazole. A fungicide used to control a range of diseases including mildew, bunts and smuts.
Trianion of N(6)-(UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl)-D-lysine; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons and 2 double bonds.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of omega-hydroxy-15-methyl-palmitic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons, 2 double bonds and a hydroxy group at C2.
An omega-hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of omega-hydroxyphytanic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 25 carbons with a hydroxy group at C2.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 25 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 25 carbons, 2 double bonds and a hydroxy group at C2.
A member of the class of triazoles that is 1-chloro-4-(3-phenylpropyl)benzene substituted at position 3 of the propyl moiety by cyano and 1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl groups.
4-(4-chlorophenyl)-2-phenyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)butanenitrile that is the (S)-enantiomer of fenbuconazole.
4-(4-chlorophenyl)-2-phenyl-2-(1,2,4-triazol-1-ylmethyl)butanenitrile that is the (R)-enantiomer of fenbuconazole.

A member of the class of quinazolines that is 6-fluoroquinazolin-4-one carrying additional 1,2,4-triazol-1-yl and 2,4-dichlorophenyl substituents at positions 2 and 3 respectively. A fungicide used to control Ascomycetes, Deuteromycetes and Basidiomycetes spp. on cereals, beets and fruit.
An enoate ester that is the methyl ester of (2E,3Z,5E)-6-(4-chloro-3-methoxyphenyl)-2-(methoxymethylene)-3-methylhexa-3,5-dienoic acid.
Any  alpha-amino acid which is not a member of the group of 23 proteinogenic amino acids.

A polysaccharide phosphate composed of a backbone of alpha-D-glucose residues connected by phosphodiester linkages between positions 1 and 4 of adjacent residues; structure of the Neisseria meningitidis X capsular polysaccharide.
The organic sodium salt of 3-aminopropyl 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucose-1-phosphate

A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (2R,4R)- and (2S,4S)-tubulozole. A synthetic anticancer drug that interferes with the structure and function of microtubules in both interphase and mitotic cells.
The organophosphate oxoanion formed by proton loss from the phospho group of 3-aminopropyl N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine-1-phosphate.
An amino sugar phosphate that is alpha-D-glucosamine linked glycosidically to a (3-aminopropoxy)(hydroxy)phosphoryl group.
A carbamate ester that is the ethyl ester of [4-({[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(imidazol-1-ylmethyl)-1,3-dioxolan-4-yl]methyl}sulfanyl)phenyl]carbamic acid.
An ethyl [4-({[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(imidazol-1-ylmethyl)-1,3-dioxolan-4-yl]methyl}sulfanyl)phenyl]carbamate in which both stereocentres have R-configuration.
An ethyl [4-({[2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(imidazol-1-ylmethyl)-1,3-dioxolan-4-yl]methyl}sulfanyl)phenyl]carbamate in which both stereocentres have S-configuration.
A polyketide isolated from fungi that is a potent inhibitor of fungal and mammalian squalene synthase.
A hydroxy fatty acid that is palmitic (hexadecanoic) acid carrying a single hydroxy substituent at position 15.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 15-hydroxypalmitic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A hydroxy fatty acid that is palmitic (hexadecanoic) acid carrying a single hydroxy substituent at position 14.
A hydroxy fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of 14-hydroxypalmitic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol(1-) which has a steroyl group as the acyl group at position 2.
The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed by loss of a proton from the carboxy group of N-acetyl-D-muramoyl-L-alanine; principal microspecies at pH 7.3.
A UDP-glycopeptide in which the glycopeptide component consists of N(6)-(N-acetyl-alpha-D-muramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl)-D-lysine, joined to UDP via a glycosyl diphosphate bond.
A proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of L-alanine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of L-alanine by a heteroatom.
A non-proteinogenic amino acid derivative resulting from reaction of D-alanine at the amino group or the carboxy group, or from the replacement of any hydrogen of D-alanine by a heteroatom.
A organonitrogen heterocyclic compound consisting of 2,3,1-benzodiazaborinine substituted at positions 1 and 2 by hydroxy and 4-toluenesufonyl groups respectively.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid that is L-alanine in which a hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by an acyl group.
